EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to taxation; providing for the issuance of
transferable tax credits and the partial abatement of
certain taxes for certain projects of single-family
residences; exempting such residences from the taxes on
real property and transfers of such residences from the
taxes on transfers of real property in certain
circumstances; prohibiting the sale of such residences to
certain corporate investors; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, financial institutions and other employers are required to
2 pay an excise tax (the modified business tax) on wages paid by them. (NRS
3 363A.130, 363B.110) Existing law provides for the imposition and administration
4 of sales and use taxes pursuant to the Sales and Use Tax Act and the Local School
5 Support Tax Law. (Chapters 372 and 374 of NRS) Any amendment to the Local
6 School Support Tax Law also applies to other sales and use taxes imposed under
7 existing law. (NRS 354.705, 374A.020, 376A.060, 377.040, 377A.030, 377B.110,
8 543.600; and various special and local acts) Sections 2-13 of this bill authorize the
9 Housing Division of the Department of Business and Industry to approve
10 applications for the issuance of transferable tax credits and granting of abatements
11 of the excise tax on employers other than financial institutions or local sales and
12 use taxes imposed pursuant to the Local School Support Tax Law that are
13 submitted by a project sponsor engaged in a project for the acquisition,
14 development and construction of single-family residences to be sold for the direct
15 cost of the residences to households who will occupy the residences and whose
16 income is less than 130 percent of the area median income. Section 9 authorizes the
17 project sponsor, on behalf of the project, to apply to the Division for these tax
